    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <head>84. Memorandum by Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_LMR2" type="from"
                        >Laird</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d84fn1">Source: Washington National Records
                        Center, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 330, Accession 74–0045, Signer’s
                        Copies October 1969. Secret. Marked “Revised by Col RE <persName
                            corresp="#p_PR11">Pursley</persName> 25 Oct 69.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-10-28">October 28, 1969</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list>
                    <head>MEMORANDUM FOR</head>
                    <item>Secretaries of the Military Departments</item>
                    <item>Chairman, Joint Chiefs of Staff</item>
                    <item>Director of Defense Research and Engineering</item>
                    <item>Assistant Secretaries of Defense</item>
                    <item>Assistants to the Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>Directors of the Defense Agencies</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Defense Program Review Committee</item>
                </list>
                <p>National Security Decision Memorandum 26<note n="2" xml:id="d84fn2">
                        <ref target="#d79">Document 79</ref>.</note> established the Defense Program
                    Review Committee to assist the President in carrying out his responsibilities
                    for the conduct of national security affairs. The membership of the Defense
                    Program Review Committee is: <list>
                        <item>The Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs
                            (Chairman)</item>
                        <item>The Under Secretary of State</item>
                        <item>The Deputy Secretary of Defense</item>
                        <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                        <item>The Chairman, Joint Chiefs of Staff</item>
                        <item>The Chairman, Council of Economic Advisers</item>
                        <item>The Director of the Bureau of the Budget</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Additionally, other agencies may be represented at the discretion of the Chairman
                    depending upon the issue under consideration.</p>
                <p>This Committee was established by the President at my request to review <hi
                        rend="italic">major</hi> Defense issues requiring Presidential
                    determination. <pb facs="0208" n="177" xml:id="pg_177"/> Major defense issues
                    should be interpreted to include only those select and broad national policy
                    matters in which the highest level military, political, and economic
                    considerations are involved.</p>
                <p>The Committee was not established to monitor Department of Defense on-going
                    internal operations, programs, or budgeting processes. The basic Department of
                    Defense program proposals and decisions will continue to be developed through
                    established Defense procedures, and the operations of the Department will
                    continue to be administered through established command channels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LMR2">Mel Laird</persName>
                        <note n="3" xml:id="d84fn3">Printed from a copy with this stamped
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
